HEADWORD: Metempirical
<hw>Met`em*pir"ic*al</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref. <ets>met-</ets> +
<ets>empiric</ets>, <ets>-ical</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Metaph.)</fld>
<def>Related, or belonging, to the objects of knowledge within the
province of metempirics.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>If then the empirical designates the province we include within
the range of science, the province we exclude may be fitly styled the
<qex>metempirical</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>G. H. Lewes.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Metempiricism</ent>⟦br⟧
